  "prompt": "Can I get into an ivy league school with no extracurriculars at all?",
  "response": "While it is technically possible to get into an Ivy League school without any extracurriculars, it would be extremely challenging. Ivy League schools typically look for well-rounded students who demonstrate not just academic excellence, but also leadership, dedication, and interests outside of the classroom. Extracurricular activities provide insight into a student's passions, skills, and ability to contribute to the campus community.\n\nIf a student has exceptional academic achievements, high standardized test scores, and strong letters of recommendation, they might still be considered, but they would be competing against many other applicants who have robust extracurricular profiles. Generally, a balanced application that showcases a range of talents, interests, and achievements tends to be more appealing to admissions committees.",
